    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Leith Hill Place | Dorking</placeName>
                    <date>Aug 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Bentham</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I thank you cordially for your most kind letter, &amp; I can say with entire truth that it has given me many times more pleasure than my election as member of the Institut.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
                    <p> Believe me with the highest respect. | Yours sincerely &amp; gratefully | Charles Darwin.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Leith … Dorking] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 more] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘the’ </note>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11642.xml">letter from George Bentham, 7 August 1878</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11642.xml">letter from George Bentham, 7 August 1878</ref>. CD was elected a corresponding member of the botanical section of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_15.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Académie des sciences</ref> of the Institut de France on 5 August 1878 (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11640A.xml">letter from J.-B. Dumas and Joseph Bertrand, 5 August 1878</ref> and n. 2).</note>
        </div>     
         
